videos.description: The Troy Trojans force 5 turnovers in the R+L Carriers New Orleans Bowl and come up with a win over North Texas, 50-30.
videos.title: Troy thumps North Texas in the Big Easy

location: Sam Boyd Stadium, Las Vegas, NV

videos.description: The Thundering Herd take down the Rams 31-28 moving Marshall to its 6th consecutive bowl win, the longest active stream in the FBS. Tyler King marked the longest run in the history of the Gildan New Mexico Bowl.
videos.title: The Thundering Herd marks the longest bowl win streak in the FBS

videos.description: Middle Tennessee led the majority of the way,  but had to hold off several Arkansas State comebacks to win the Raycom Media Camellia Bowl 35-30.
videos.title: Middle Tennessee holds off multiple Arkansas State comebacks

videos.description: FAU easily handles Akron in the Cheribundi Tart Cherry Boca Raton Bowl with a 50-3 victory. Jason Driskel led the Owls with 270 passing yards and 4 total touchdowns while Devin Singletary contributed with 124 rushing yards and three scores.
videos.title: Jason Driskel and FAU dominate Akron in Boca Raton Bowl

videos.description: Hopes were high in the DXL Frisco Bowl for SMU's new head coach Sonny Dykes in his first game against Louisiana Tech, but costly turnovers and an electric Bulldog offense led to the 51-10 Tech to win.
videos.title: Turnovers the name of the game in Frisco

videos.description: Temple entered its 3rd consecutive bowl as the winningest senior class in school history and would go home victorious in the Bad Boy Mowers Gasparilla Bowl defeating FIU 28-3.
videos.title: Temple's winningest senior class in school history secures bowl win, 28-3

videos.description: Ohio comes away with a dominate 41-6 win over UAB during the Popeyes Bahamas Bowl. Dorian Brown led the offense with 4 rushing touchdowns tying the Bahamas Bowl record.
videos.title: Ohio ties Bahamas Bowl touchdown record

videos.description: Wyoming wins its first bowl since 2009 in a 37-14 victory over Central Michigan. The Cowboys' defense held the Chippewas to 18 total rushing yards and forced a school-record eight turnovers.
videos.title: Wyoming forces a school record 8 turnovers

videos.description: South Florida scores a touchdown with just 16 seconds left to defeat Texas Tech 38-34 in the Birmingham Bowl. USF's Quinton Flowers threw for 311 yards and 4 touchdowns while rushing for 106 yards and 1 touchdown.
videos.title: South Florida beats Texas Tech in a Thriller

videos.description: Army and San Diego State combine for nearly 700 rushing yards in the Lockheed Martin Armed Forces Bowl, but it's the Black Knights that come out on top 42-35.
videos.title: Army beats San Diego State with late 2-Point Conversion

location: Amon G. Carter Stadium, Fort Worth, TX

videos.description: Appalachian State shuts out Toledo with a 34-0 win in the Dollar General Bowl. Jalin Moore ushered in three Mountaineer touchdowns on 125 rushing yards.
videos.title: App State hands Toledo its first shut out since 2009

location: Hawaiian Tel Federal Credit Union Field , Honolulu, HI

videos.description: Utah went up early and never looked back to take the Zaxby's Heart of Dallas Bowl, 30-14. Utah's offense, led by Zack Moss' 150 yards, ran all over a Mountaineer team that has been hampered by injuries all season.
videos.title: West Virginia can't stop high-powered Utes offense

videos.description: Duke got out to a 14-0 lead early and squashed a potential comeback by Northern Illinois to win the Quick Lane Bowl, 36-14. Quarterback Daniel Jones threw for two touchdown passes and added another on the ground to lead the Blue Devils.
videos.title: Duke makes fast work of Northern Illinois in the Quick Lane Bowl

videos.description: Florida State defeated Southern Miss in the Walk On's Independence Bowl, score-score. James Blackman was the catalyst for the Seminole offense, 262 total yards and 4 touchdowns.
videos.title: Seminoles overpower the Golden Eagles in a 42-13 victory

videos.description: In a game where neither team led by more than a touchdown, Iowa outlasted Boston College to win the New Era Pinstripe Bowl, 27-20. Iowa's defense forced three turnovers as Kirk Ferentz moved into a tie with Hayden Fry as Iowa's leader in all time wins.
videos.title: Turnovers the key to Iowa's thrilling 27-20 Pinstripe Bowl victory

videos.description: After giving up a touchdown on the first play of the game, Navy dominated the rest of the Northrop Grumman Military Bowl, 49-7. Malcolm Perry led the Midshipmen with 114 yards on the ground while Zach Abey added five touchdowns on the day.
videos.title: Navy wins the Military Bowl without completing a single pass

location: Navy-Marine Corps Memorial Stadium, Annapolis, MD

videos.description: Both teams were looking to finish off the year with a 10 win season and the Cowboys came out on top as Oklahoma State took down Virginia Tech in the Camping World Bowl. Mason Rudolph finished off his career as a Cowboy with 351 passing yards and 2 touchdowns in a 30-21 victory.
videos.title: Mason Rudolph lights it up in his final game

videos.description: Back in 2015 the Horned Frogs came back from being down 31 against Oregon in the Alamo Bowl. This time they were down 18 against Stanford but they still completed the comeback at the same venue. Kenny Hill led the way with 314 passing yards and 4 total touchdowns to beat the Cardinal 39-37.
videos.title: The Horned Frogs are the comeback kings of the Alamo Bowl

videos.description: Wake Forest came out on top 55-52 over Texas A&M in a record setting game for plays (191), yards (1,260), and points (107). Quarterback John Wolford had 400 yards passing for 4 touchdowns in his finale as a Demon Deacon.
videos.title: Wake Forest squeaks out the win in record setting Belk Bowl

location: Bank of America Stadium, Charlotte, NC
Sun Bowl Stadium, El Paso, TX

videos.description: After an injury-plagued first half, Northwestern prevails to a 24-23 win over Kentucky. Justin Jackson led the offensive charge with 157 rushing yards and 2 touchdowns.
videos.title: Music City Bowl winner crowned on final play

videos.description: Interim Coach Greg Knox and freshman quarterback Keytaon Thompson lead the Bulldogs to a victory over Louisville in the Taxslayer bowl. Thomson ran for 148 yards and 3 touchdowns on the day while Mark McLaurin picked off Lamar Jackson 3 times to solidify the Bulldogs 31-27 victory.
videos.title: Mark McLaurin picks off Lamar Jackson 3 times in the Taxslayer Bowl

videos.description: Despite turning the ball over on the 1 yard-line late in the game, Iowa State held on in the last moments of the game to beat Memphis 21-20 in the Liberty Bowl. Kyle Kempt lead the Cyclones with 314 passing yards and 2 touchdowns.
videos.title: Iowa State holds on in final moments of the Liberty Bowl

location: Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium, Memphis, TN
University of Phoenix Stadium, Glendale, AZ
Hard Rock Stadium, Miami Gardens, FL

videos.description: South Carolina comes back from being down 16 to take care of Michigan in the Outback Bowl. The Gamecocks forced 5 turnovers late in the second half to solidify their 26-19 victory.
videos.title: Michigan miscues sink Wolverines

videos.description: UCF secures a storybook ending to its undefeated season beating Auburn 34-27 in the Chick-fil-A Peach Bowl. The Knights defense helped shut down the Tigers with 5 sacks in the first half.
videos.title: UCF remains the only undefeated team in the FBS
